## 🗺️ What is AI Engineering?

### Real-World Analogy
> Think of traditional software engineering as **building a car from scratch**.  
> An AI Engineer gets a **pre-built, highly intelligent engine** (the LLM) and their job is to:
> - Wire it up to real systems
> - Make it useful for real users
> - Ship it reliably at scale

You don't train the model. You **orchestrate** it.

