## 💻 Core Pattern — It's Just an API Call!

The mental model you already have **transfers directly**.

### C# (what you already know)
```csharp
// Calling a Payment API — familiar pattern
var payload = new StringContent(
    JsonSerializer.Serialize(new { amount = 100 }),
    Encoding.UTF8, "application/json"
);
var response = await httpClient.PostAsync(
    "https://payment-api.com/charge", payload
);
var result = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
Console.WriteLine(result);
```

### Python (what you're learning)
```python
# Calling an LLM API — same concept, intelligent output!
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI()

response = client.chat.completions.create(
    model="gpt-4",
    messages=[
        {"role": "user", "content": "Summarise this report in 3 bullet points"}
    ]
)

print(response.choices[0].message.content)
```

> 🔑 **Key Insight:** Same mental model → `call → response`  
> Only difference: the response is **intelligent text** instead of structured data.

