## 🔧 Dev Setup — Step by Step

### ✅ Checklist
- [ ] Python 3.11+ installed
- [ ] `pip` and `venv` working
- [ ] VS Code + Python extension installed
- [ ] `.env` file pattern understood (never commit API keys!)
- [ ] Groq free API key obtained → https://console.groq.com
- [ ] Git set up

---

### Step 1 — Virtual Environment

```bash
# Create venv
python -m venv .venv

# Activate — Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate

# Activate — Mac/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate

# Install packages
pip install openai python-dotenv fastapi uvicorn
```

> 🔵 **C# Parallel:** `venv` = your `.csproj` NuGet package boundary.  
> Each project gets its own isolated dependencies. Same idea!

---

### Step 2 — API Keys the Right Way

```bash
# .env file — NEVER commit this to Git!
GROQ_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

```python
# Python — Load your key safely
from dotenv import load_dotenv
import os

load_dotenv()
api_key = os.getenv("GROQ_API_KEY")
```

```csharp
// C# Equivalent — you already know this!
var apiKey = configuration["GROQ_API_KEY"];
// or
var apiKey = Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("GROQ_API_KEY");
```

